Subject: Bill Henderson (footballer born 1898) 
To: Jimmy
Content:
William "Bill" Henderson (1898 in Edinburgh  1964) was a Scottish footballer who played as a forward. Born in Edinburgh, he played for Airdrie before joining Manchester United in 1921. In 36 matches for Manchester United, he scored 17 goals. In 1925, he was transferred to Preston North End, before spending time on the books of Clapton Orient, Heart of Midlothian, Morton, Torquay United and Exeter City.
